'''Armin Gigović''' ({{IPA|bs|ǎrmin ɡîːgoʋitɕ|pron}}; born 6 April 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Swiss Super League]] club [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]. Born in Sweden, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Gigović started his professional career at [[Helsingborgs IF]], before joining [[FC Rostov|Rostov]] in 2020, who loaned him back to Helsingborgs IF in 2022, to [[Odense Boldklub|OB]] later that year and to [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in 2023. The following year, he signed with [[Holstein Kiel]]. In 2025, he was transferred to Young Boys.

A former Swedish youth international, Gigović also made his senior international debut for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]], before switching his allegiance to Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2024, earning 20 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Gigović started playing football at [[Landskrona BoIS]], before joining [[Helsingborgs IF|Helsingborgs IF's youth setup]] in 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/nogometni-savez-bih-razgovarao-s-talentovanim-gigovicem-o-igranju-za-zmajeve/210222075|title=Nogometni savez BiH razgovarao s talentovanim Gigovićem o igranju za Zmajeve|website=klix.ba|date=22 February 2021|access-date=23 February 2021|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[IK Sirius Fotboll|IK Sirius]] on 15 July 2019 at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://expressen.se/kvallsposten/sport/fotboll/allsvenskan/henkes-helsingborg-fortfarande-obesegrat|title=Henkes Helsingborg fortfarande obesegrat|website=expressen.se|date=15 July 2019|access-date=18 July 2019|language=sv}}</ref> On 6 July 2020, he scored his first professional goal against [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://expressen.se/kvallsposten/sport/fotboll/allsvenskan/han-far-en-riktig-mardromsoppning|title=Första målen för året – när HIF kom ikapp|website=expressen.se|date=6 July 2020|access-date=8 July 2020|language=sv}}</ref>

===Rostov===
In October 2020, Gigović signed a five-year deal with Russian side [[FC Rostov|Rostov]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/potencijalni-18-godisnji-reprezentativac-bih-armin-gigovic-novi-clan-rostova/201015151|title=Potencijalni 18-godišnji reprezentativac BiH Armin Gigović novi član Rostova|website=klix.ba|date=15 October 2020|access-date=18 October 2020|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the team against [[FC Khimki|Khimki]] on 25 October.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/312138-dennis-hadzikadunic-odigrao-svih-90-minuta-za-rostov-debitovao-i-armin-gigovic|title=Dennis Hadžikadunić odigrao svih 90 minuta za Rostov, debitovao i Armin Gigović|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=25 October 2020|access-date=28 October 2020|language=bs}}</ref> On 17 March 2021, he scored his first goal for Rostov in a triumph over [[FC Rotor Volgograd|Rotor Volgograd]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/638293/armin-gigovic-postigao-prvijenac-za-rostov|title=Armin Gigović postigao prvijenac za Rostov|website=avaz.ba|date=17 March 2021|access-date=18 March 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

In March 2022, Gigović was loaned to his former club Helsingborgs IF until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/potencijalni-reprezentativac-bih-napustio-rusiju-i-vratio-se-kuci/422080|title=Potencijalni reprezentativac BiH napustio Rusiju i vratio se kući|website=sportsport.ba|date=31 March 2022|access-date=1 April 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

In August 2022, he was sent on a six-month loan to Danish outfit [[Odense Boldklub|OB]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tipsbladet.dk/nyhed/superliga/ob-henter-dagens-anden-midtbanespiller|title=OB henter dagens anden midtbanespiller|website=tipsbladet.dk|date=31 August 2022|access-date=1 September 2022|language=da}}</ref>

In January 2023, he was loaned to [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] for the remainder of the campaign. In June, his loan was extended for an additional season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/potencijalni-zmaj-na-kojeg-racuna-i-hadzibegic-potpisao|title=Potencijalni Zmaj na kojeg računa i Hadžibegić potpisao|website=sportske.ba|date=5 June 2023|access-date=8 June 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

===Holstein Kiel===
In July 2024, Gigović was transferred to German team [[Holstein Kiel]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/novi-reprezentativac-bosne-i-hercegovine-potpisao-za-ekipu-iz-bundeslige|title=Novi reprezentativac Bosne i Hercegovine potpisao za ekipu iz Bundeslige|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=23 July 2024|access-date=23 July 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the squad on 31 August against [[VfL Wolfsburg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/bundesliga-demirovic-usao-s-klupe-tabakovic-i-gigovic-upisali-debitantske-nastupe|title=Bundesliga: Demirović ušao s klupe, Tabaković i Gigović upisali debitantske nastupe|website=sportske.ba|date=31 August 2024|access-date=1 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref> On 14 September, he scored his first goal for Holstein Kiel against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/armin-gigovic-postigao-prvijenac-u-bundesligi-zmaj-pogodio-protiv-velikog-bayerna-video|title=Armin Gigović postigao prvijenac u Bundesligi: Zmaj pogodio protiv velikog Bayerna|website=n1info.ba|date=14 September 2024|access-date=17 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

===Young Boys===
In August 2025, Gigović moved to Swiss outfit [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] on a contract until June 2029.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/gigovic-i-zvanicno-igrac-young-boysa-visina-transfera-mnogo-veca-nego-sto-se-spominjalo/3484444|title=Gigović i zvanično igrač Young Boysa, visina transfera mnogo veća nego što se spominjalo|website=fokus.ba|date=12 August 2025|access-date=13 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted officially for the side in a [[2025–26 Swiss Cup#First round|Swiss Cup]] game against Courtételle on 17 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/armin-gigovic-debitovao-u-ubjedljivoj-pobjedi-novog-kluba|title=Armin Gigović debitovao u ubjedljivoj pobjedi novog kluba|website=scsport.ba|date=17 August 2025|access-date=18 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 28 August, he scored a brace in a [[2025–26 UEFA Europa League#Play-off round|UEFA Europa League qualifier]] against [[ŠK Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]], which were his first goals for Young Boys.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/479486-armin-gigovic-postigao-dva-gola-za-young-boys|title=Armin Gigović postigao dva gola za Young Boys|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=28 August 2025|access-date=28 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He made his league debut on 31 August against [[FC Lugano|Lugano]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/479998-katicu-tri-boda-sa-schalkeom-slavio-i-gigovic-stevanovic-pogodio-i-asistirao|title=Katiću tri boda sa Schalkeom, slavio i Gigović, Stevanović pogodio i asistirao|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=31 August 2025|access-date=1 September 2025|language=bs}}</ref> Five months later, he scored his first league goal in a deafeat of [[FC Zürich|Zürich]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/499476-gigovic-strijelac-u-pobjedi-young-boysa|title=Gigović strijelac u pobjedi Young Boysa|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=1 February 2026|access-date=1 February 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
After representing [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] at all youth levels and [[Captain (association football)|captaining]] them at the [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21 level]] under coach [[Daniel Bäckström (footballer)|Daniel Bäckström]], Gigović made his senior international debut in a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] game against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] on 12 January 2023. However, in April 2024, he decided that he would play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in the future.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/gigovic-otkrio-kako-je-otpisao-svedjane-rekao-sam-im-da-zelim-samo-svoju-zemlju/240531122|title=Gigović otkrio kako je "otpisao" Šveđane: Rekao sam im da želim samo svoju zemlju|website=klix.ba|date=31 May 2024|access-date=1 June 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In May, his request to change sports citizenship from Swedish to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/spahic-gigovic-je-napravio-veliki-pritisak-na-savez-svedske-i-mi-smo-dobili-papire|title=Spahić: Gigović je napravio veliki pritisak na savez Švedske i mi smo dobili papire|website=scsport.ba|date=16 May 2024|access-date=17 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref> Later that month, he received his first senior call up, for friendly matches against [[England national football team|England]] and [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/ovo-je-barbarezov-spisak-za-englesku-i-italiju-pozvano-sedam-novih-zmajeva/545686|title=Ovo je Barbarezov spisak za Englesku i Italiju: Pozvano sedam novih Zmajeva|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=16 May 2024|access-date=18 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 3 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/engleska-slavila-protiv-bih-zmajevi-u-barbarezovom-debiju-za-pola-sata-potopljeni-u-newcastleu/189628|title=Engleska slavila protiv BiH: Zmajevi u Barbarezovom debiju za pola sata potopljeni u Newcastleu|website=faktor.ba|date=3 June 2024|access-date=4 June 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

On 21 March 2025, in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Romania national football team|Romania]], he scored his first senior international goal, which secured the victory for his team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/962742/pocetak-kvalifikacija-kao-iz-snova-zmajevi-srusili-rumuniju-usred-bukuresta|title=Početak kvalifikacija kao iz snova: Zmajevi srušili Rumuniju usred Bukurešta|website=avaz.ba|date=21 March 2025|access-date=23 March 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Gigović was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Gigović's younger brother Ervin is also a professional footballer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tvarenasport.ba/fudbal/brat-bh-reprezentativca-produzio-saradnju-sa-svedskim-klubom|title=Brat bh. reprezentativca produžio sadadnju sa švedskim klubom|website=tvarenasport.ba|date=3 January 2025|access-date=3 January 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

